english:
  title: Inscribed on the Western River Pavilion
  author: Kwon U
  language: eng
  text: |-
    I have grown to love this river pavilion so.
    Climbed high, I linger and cannot turn back.
    Merchant sails descend and rest upon the shore,
    While fishing boats rise with the turning tide.
    At the far reaches, cold mist gathers thick,
    And distant mountains glow with evening's flame.
    My calculating heart has fully dissolved—
    Fish and birds, suspect me not.
  footnotes:
    - The 'calculating heart' (機心) refers to worldly ambitions and the machinations of the human mind—a Buddhist and Taoist concept of the burden one must shed to achieve spiritual tranquility.
    - The final couplet addresses the creatures of nature, suggesting the speaker has transcended the human condition of suspicion and competition, now at peace with the natural world.
